Package: nacopula
Version: 0.7-8
Date: 2011-05-24
LastChanged: $LastChangedRevision$; $LastChangedDate$
Title: Nested Archimedean Copulas
Description: An R package for working with nested Archimedean copulas. 
In particular, providing a procedure for computing function values and cube volumes, 
characteristics such as Kendall's tau and tail dependence coefficients, efficient 
sampling algorithms, various estimation procedures, and goodness-of-fit tests. 
The package also contains certain interesting univariate distributions, 
e.g., the Sibuya distribution.
Author: Marius Hofert <marius.hofert@math.ethz.ch> and Martin Maechler
Maintainer: Martin Maechler <maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch>
Depends: methods, stats4
Imports: gsl, ADGofTest, stabledist
Suggests: lattice, MASS, sfsmisc, Rmpfr (>= 0.2-6), bbmle
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: yes
Encoding: UTF-8
